Based on the provided documentation, the RideFlow AI project is an end-to-end intelligent ride optimization platform designed for the mobility and smart transportation domain. It aims to balance demand and driver supply, reduce cancellations, optimize pricing dynamically, and improve safety and customer experience.The project is structured into three distinct modules across five implementation phases:Module 1: Machine Learning (System Awareness)This module focuses on the core predictive capabilities of the ride-hailing system:Ride Demand Prediction: Predicts where and when ride requests will occur using time-series forecasting and regression.Driver Supply Prediction: Forecasts available drivers per zone to identify potential imbalances.Demand-Supply Gap & Dynamic Pricing: Calculates shortages and generates a surge multiplier (typically between 1.0–3.0) to balance the market.Ride Cancellation Prediction: A classification task that predicts the probability of a ride being cancelled based on factors like ETA and price.Module 2: Deep Learning (Precision Systems)This layer adds high-accuracy predictive and monitoring capabilities:ETA Prediction: Uses Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) models to predict accurate driver arrival times.Driver Behavior Monitoring: Employs Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) to detect unsafe behaviors like phone usage or rash driving using image/video data.Demand Hotspot Detection: Utilizes transfer learning with pretrained models (e.g., ResNet) and geospatial embeddings to identify high-demand zones.Module 3: NLP & Generative AI (Decision & Interaction)The final layer handles user interaction and intelligent matching:Feedback Intelligence System: Uses BERT to perform sentiment analysis and issue classification on customer and driver reviews.AI-Powered Ride Matching Assistant: An LLM-based system (often using RAG) that recommends the best driver based on quality, ETA, and cancellation risk.AI Chatbot & Multilingual Support: Provides real-time support for booking and navigation in English, Tamil, and Hindi using LLMs and translation tools.Evaluation & Success MetricsThe project is evaluated based on both technical and business performance:Technical Metrics: Includes RMSE and R² for regression; Accuracy, F1-score, and ROC-AUC for classification; and Precision/Recall for CNN models.Business Results: A successful implementation aims for a 20-30% reduction in cancellations, 25% improved ETA accuracy, and increased customer satisfaction.Deliverables: Requirements include modular source code, EDA notebooks, a Streamlit dashboard, a FastAPI backend, and an architecture diagram.
